<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="564" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,361,749]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,614,640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carlgren" authorityYear="1914" box="[324,470,614,640]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actinernidae" genus="Synhalcurias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[324,470,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">Synhalcurias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recognized as monotypic since it was established by 
<bibRefCitation author="Carlgren, O." box="[1200,1382,614,640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" pagination="49 - 71" refId="ref5950" refString="Carlgren, O. (1914) On the genus Porponia and related genera, Scottish National Antarctic Expedition. Transactions of the Royal Society of Edinburgh, 50, 49 - 71. https: // doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0080456800017270" type="journal article" year="1914">Carlgren (1914)</bibRefCitation>
(see also 
<bibRefCitation author="Carlgren, O." box="[203,373,650,676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" pagination="1 - 121" refId="ref6039" refString="Carlgren, O. (1949) A survey of the Ptychodactiaria, Corallimorpharia and Actiniaria. Kungliga Svenska Vetenskapsakademiens Handlingar, 1, 1 - 121." type="journal article" year="1949">Carlgren, 1949</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Fautin, D. G." box="[384,530,650,677]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" pagination="1 - 449" refId="ref6154" refString="Fautin, D. G. (2016) Catalog to families, genera, and species of orders Actiniaria and Corallimorpharia (Cnidaria: Anthozoa). Zootaxa, 4145 (1), 1 - 449. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4145.1.1" type="journal article" year="2016">Fautin, 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, we describe a second species for this genus, 
<taxonomicName authority="Izumi &amp; Yanagi, 2021" authorityName="Izumi &amp; Yanagi" authorityYear="2021" box="[1190,1306,650,676]" class="Anthozoa" family="Actinernidae" genus="Synhalcurias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Actiniaria" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="species" species="kakahui" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1190,1306,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">S. kakahui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1312,1401,650,676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1312,1401,650,676]" pageId="3" pageNumber="564" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
To incorporate this additional species, we rearranged the diagnosis as below: 1) adding the cnidom; 2) added the case that not nematocyst batteries in the column; 3) revised that all mesenteries perfect (instead of “almost all”).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
